  <h1>Healthy BMI for Women: An Age-Specific Guide</h1>
  <div class="meta">Last updated: July 2026 &nbsp;·&nbsp; 7 min read &nbsp;·&nbsp; Reviewed for accuracy</div>

  <p>BMI is calculated the same way for everyone, but what counts as a healthy result is more nuanced for women. Hormones, reproductive stages, body composition, and ethnicity all influence how BMI should be interpreted in a female context. This guide breaks down what healthy BMI looks like for women at different life stages — and what other measurements matter just as much.</p>

  <p>You can also use our <a href="bmi-calculator.html">free BMI Calculator</a> to find your own number instantly.</p>

